Curry & Sriracha Roasted Cauliflower

1 head cauliflower
1-2 tbsp sesame, coconut, or olive oil
1 heaping tbsp sriracha
1 heaping tbsp curry powder
generous dash of garlic powder

Preheat oven to 425F. Cut cauliflower into florets and place in large bowl. Combine oil, sriracha, curry, and garlic powder in a small bowl. Pour over cauliflower and coat well. Place in a single layer on a roasting pan lined with parchment paper or lightly greased with oil if needed. Cook for 45 min, stirring every 15 min.

Note: add more seasoning to taste
